%description:
Deterministic MLDv2 host-behavior test (RFC 3810 §6).

Tests the MLDv2 host (listener) state-change and current-state report behavior via
Cmdenv log assertions with a fixed RNG seed. Membership is driven by a real app
(UdpSink with multicastGroup), the production path. This is the same scenario as
MLD_host_basic.test but with **.ipv6.mld.typename="Mldv2".

HOSTv2-01 (State-Change Report on join, ASM/any-source):
  host1 runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1:2:3" (no multicastSources), which
  is an any-source (EXCLUDE{}) join. The socket join at t=0 fires
  ipv6MulticastChangeSignal -> Mldv2::multicastSourceListChanged. The per-(if,group)
  filter transitions INCLUDE() -> EXCLUDE(), so the host emits a State-Change Report
  carrying a CHANGE_TO_EXCLUDE_MODE (TO_EX) record (RFC 3810 §5.2.12, §6.1).

HOSTv2-02 (Current-State Report on a General Query):
  The router has multicastForwarding=true (real querier). With startupQueryInterval=2s
  it sends its first General MLDv2 Query (multicastAddress=::, empty source list) to
  ff02::1 at ~t=2s. All nodes on the shared Ethernet segment receive it. The host
  schedules a uniform(0, maxRespDelay) delayed response and, when the timer fires,
  sends a Current-State Report with a MODE_IS_EXCLUDE record for ff0e::1:2:3
  (RFC 3810 §6.1, report generation point 1).

HOSTv2-03 (State-Change Report on leave):
  host1's UdpSink has stopTime=5s, which closes the socket and fires the membership
  change EXCLUDE() -> INCLUDE() (no listeners). The host emits a State-Change Report
  carrying a CHANGE_TO_INCLUDE_MODE (TO_IN) record (RFC 3810 §6.1).

Network: host1 and router on a shared EthernetHub. Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns
addresses. Both nodes have hasMld=true and mld.typename="Mldv2". The router is a real
querier (router.multicastForwarding=true at node level so NetworkLayerNodeBase
propagates it to the routing table). DAD is disabled for fast startup; RNG seed pinned.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network Mldv2HostBasicNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = Mldv2HostBasicNetwork
sim-time-limit = 10s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespDelay) in the host timer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLDv2 on all nodes
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
**.ipv6.mld.typename = "Mldv2"
# RFC 3810 6.1: each State-Change Report is sent [Robustness Variable] (=2) times.
# Shrink the host's Unsolicited Report Interval so the retransmission of the join
# (TO_EX) and leave (TO_IN) changes fires promptly within the 10s run (seed pinned above).
**.host1.ipv6.mld.unsolicitedReportInterval = 0.5s
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no 1s+ delay before addresses are ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# HOSTv2-01/03: host1 joins ff0e::1:2:3 via UdpSink (any-source join -> EXCLUDE{}).
# Socket join fires ipv6MulticastChangeSignal -> Mldv2::multicastSourceListChanged.
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1:2:3"
# HOSTv2-03: host1 leaves at t=5s (socket close fires the EXCLUDE()->INCLUDE() change).
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

# HOSTv2-02: enable the real querier on the router (multicastForwarding at node level
# so NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding
# to all submodules, overriding any per-submodule INI setting).
**.router.multicastForwarding = true
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 2s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 5s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-01: ASM join produces an INCLUDE()->EXCLUDE() state change on host1
%# (each EV line carries the "%C: " node-path prefix, so assert the change line and the
%#  Old/New-state continuation lines individually)
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: State of group 'ff0e::1:2:3' on interface 'eth0' has changed:
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld:     Old state: INCLUDE().
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld:     New state: EXCLUDE().

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-01: the INCLUDE->EXCLUDE change is reported as a CHANGE_TO_EXCLUDE_MODE (TO_EX) record
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Sending TO_EX report.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-01: and a Multicast Listener Report is put on the wire
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Mldv2: sending Multicast Listener Report on iface=eth0

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-02: host1 receives the router's General Query (unspecified group)
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Received Mldv2 query on interface 'eth0' for group '<unspec>'.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-02: host1 schedules a delayed response to the General Query
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Received a General Query, scheduling report with delay=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-02: when the response timer fires, host1 sends a Current-State Report (a General Query response)
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Sending response to a General Query on interface 'eth0'.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-03: on leave (t=5s) host1's filter changes EXCLUDE()->INCLUDE() ...
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld:     Old state: EXCLUDE().
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld:     New state: INCLUDE().

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-03: ... and is reported as a CHANGE_TO_INCLUDE_MODE (TO_IN) record
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Sending TO_IN report.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# HOSTv2-04 (RFC 3810 6.1): each host State-Change Report (the join TO_EX and the leave
%# TO_IN) is sent [Robustness Variable] (=2) times: the immediate report plus one
%# retransmission within the Unsolicited Report Interval. Assert host1 retransmits.
%contains: stdout
Mldv2HostBasicNetwork.host1.ipv6.mld: Retransmitting State-Change Report for group 'ff0e::1:2:3' on interface 'eth0' (1 transmission(s) left).

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Undisposed-object guard: verify no leaked cMessage or cObject at end of run
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
